    <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.8rem;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:1rem;">Commercial Reach-In Refrigerators</h2>
<img src="/images/display-fridge.jpg" alt="Display Fridge" class="product-img" loading="lazy">

    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Reach-in refrigerators are the standard workhorse of commercial kitchens. They come in single-door, double-door, and triple-door configurations and maintain temperatures between 2°C and 8°C. For Indian bakeries and restaurants, stainless steel commercial refrigerators are essential for ingredient storage, dough retardation, and prepped food.</p>
    <div class="card-grid" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
      <div class="card"><h3>Single-Door Commercial Fridge</h3>
<img src="/images/deep-freezer.jpg" alt="Deep Freezer" class="product-img" loading="lazy">
<p>150–300 litre capacity. Perfect for small bakeries, cafés, and cloud kitchens with limited floor space.</p><div class="price-tag">₹25,000 – ₹65,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Small bakeries, cloud kitchens</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Double-Door Commercial Fridge</h3><p>400–600 litre capacity. The most common commercial refrigerator size for Indian restaurants and bakeries.</p><div class="price-tag">₹55,000 – ₹1,20,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Medium bakeries, restaurants</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Triple-Door Commercial Fridge</h3><p>700–900 litre capacity. For kitchens with high ingredient turnover and large prep volumes.</p><div class="price-tag">₹1,00,000 – ₹2,00,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Large restaurants, hotel kitchens</p></div>
