    </div>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.8rem;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:1rem;">Bakery Display Counters & Cases</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Bakery display cases are refrigerated or ambient counters that showcase your products to customers. A good display counter can significantly increase impulse purchases. They come in front-service and self-service styles, and in refrigerated or non-refrigerated versions depending on what you're displaying.</p>
    <div class="card-grid" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
      <div class="card"><h3>Refrigerated Cake Display Counter</h3><p>Glass-front refrigerated display for cakes, pastries, and desserts. Maintains 4–8°C while allowing full product visibility.</p><div class="price-tag">₹35,000 – ₹1,50,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Cake shops, pastry bakeries</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Bread & Pastry Display Counter</h3><p>Ambient (non-refrigerated) display for bread, muffins, cookies, and ambient pastries. Keeps products fresh and visible.</p><div class="price-tag">₹20,000 – ₹75,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Bread bakeries, snack counters</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Curved Glass Deli Counter</h3><p>Premium curved-glass display for upscale bakeries and deli counters. Creates an elegant presentation for high-value products.</p><div class="price-tag">₹60,000 – ₹2,50,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Upscale bakeries, hotel pastry shops</p></div>
    </div>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.8rem;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:1rem;">Blast Chillers & Shock Freezers</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">A blast chiller rapidly reduces food temperature from +70°C to +3°C in under 90 minutes. For bakeries using the bake-off or par-bake model, blast chillers are essential equipment. They extend shelf life, preserve quality, and help comply with FSSAI food safety regulations for temperature-sensitive products.</p>
    <div class="card-grid" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
      <div class="card"><h3>5-Tray Blast Chiller</h3><p>Compact blast chiller for small bakeries and cloud kitchens. Handles output from a small convection oven.</p><div class="price-tag">₹1,20,000 – ₹2,50,000</div></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>10-Tray Blast Chiller</h3><p>Mid-range blast chiller for medium-scale production. Pairs well with an 8–10 tray convection oven.</p><div class="price-tag">₹2,00,000 – ₹4,50,000</div></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>20-Tray Blast Chiller</h3><p>Commercial-grade blast chiller for high-volume operations. Used in hotel kitchens, catering, and large bakeries.</p><div class="price-tag">₹4,00,000 – ₹9,00,000</div></div>
    </div>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.8rem;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:1rem;">Walk-In Cold Rooms</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">When your storage requirements exceed what reach-in refrigerators can handle, a walk-in cold room is the answer. Walk-ins are modular, constructed on-site, and can be any size. In India's hot climate, a well-insulated walk-in cold room is critical for large bakeries and restaurants handling significant quantities of perishables.</p>
    <div class="card-grid" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
